    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PET POLICY -->
  <section id="pets">
    <h2><span class="icon">üêæ</span>Pet Policy (Summary)</h2>
    <p class="subtitle">
      This is a summary only. The official WHA Pet Policy and your lease control any questions.
    </p>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Allowed Pets</span>
        <h3>Type & Size</h3>
        <ul class="key-points">
          <li>Common household pets such as small dogs, cats, birds, and fish.</li>
          <li>Weight limit: generally up to 25 lbs for dogs and cats.</li>
          <li>Pets must be registered with management before being brought into the unit.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="muted">
          Service animals and assistance animals are handled as reasonable accommodations and are not subject to
          pet fees, but must still follow behavior rules.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <span class="label label-danger">Not Allowed</span>
        <h3>Prohibited Types</h3>
        <ul class="key-points">
          <li>Reptiles, rodents (other than approved small caged animals if allowed), insects, and wild animals.</li>
          <li>Certain breeds such as pit bulls, rottweilers, chows, and boxers are not permitted.</li>
          <li>Any animal that is aggressive, unsafe, or disruptive may not remain on the property.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Requirements</span>
        <h3>Registration & Care</h3>
        <ul class="key-points">
          <li>Pets must be spayed/neutered by required age (unless medically excused).</li>
          <li>Current vaccination and local license records must be provided.</li>
          <li>Owners are responsible for cleaning up after pets and preventing damage.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <!-- TODO: Replace # with pet registration form -->
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-secondary">Request Pet Registration Packet</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BAN POLICY -->
  <section id="bans">
    <h2><span class="icon">üö´</span>Ban Policy (Summary)</h2>
    <p class="subtitle">
      Certain individuals may be banned from all WHA property to protect residents, staff, and visitors.
    </p>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="label label-danger">Who Can Be Banned</span>
        <h3>Reasons for Bans</h3>
        <ul class="key-points">
          <li>Violent or threatening actions toward residents, staff, or guests.</li>
          <li>Drug-related or other criminal activity on or affecting WHA property.</li>
          <li>Vandalism, repeated disturbances, or creating a public nuisance.</li>
          <li>Loitering or being on property with no legal right to be there.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Resident Responsibility</span>
        <h3>Hosting Banned Individuals</h3>
        <ul class="key-points">
          <li>Residents do <strong>not</strong> have the right to invite someone who is banned without written WHA approval.</li>
          <li>Allowing a banned person on the property can result in lease termination.</li>
          <li>Special limited visitation may be requested from WHA in specific situations.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <span class="label">Ban List & Appeals</span>
        <h3>Ban Lengths & Removal</h3>
        <ul class="key-points">
          <li>Ban lengths range from 6 months to lifetime, depending on the offense.</li>
          <li>One appeal may be requested in writing within the WHA timeframe.</li>
          <li>At the end of the minimum ban period, individuals may request review for removal from the list.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <!-- TODO: Replace # with a link to the posted ban list or PDF if you host it -->
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-soft">View Ban List (if available)</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

